<title>SOUTH KOREA: Seoul stock market closed for national holiday.</title>
<headline>Seoul stock market closed for national holiday.</headline>
<dateline>SEOUL 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Seoul's stock market was closed on Monday for Children's Day.</p>
<p>On Saturday, the composite stock index closed 1.23 points lower at 704.87.</p>
<p>The market will reopen on Tuesday. Brokers forecast sentiment would improve with rising liquidity stemming from last week's increase in the foreign stockholding limit.</p>
